Reasoning: The paper deals with the complexity of quantified propositional logics, which is a topic in mathematical logic and theoretical computer science. The use of alternating dependency quantified boolean formulae (ADQBF) suggests a connection to logic and complexity theory, which is reflected in the sub-category cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The study of propositional team-based logics and their extensions suggests a connection to artificial intelligence and knowledge representation, which is reflected in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The complexity analysis of the truth evaluation for ADQBF suggests a connection to computational complexity theory, which is reflected in the sub-categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the identification of fragments for which the problem is complete for the levels of the exponential hierarchy suggests a connection to discrete mathematics, which is reflected in the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
